reviews.review_text:
Great Show Great Show. Second Set will set you free of all your impending cares and worries. Guaranteed.

10 stars!

Thank you, Unknown, and thank you, Archives.org.
Mind Left Body Jam one of the best mind left body jams I've ever heard,

Excellent Fall '73 Dick was pretty spot on...The Dark Star and MLB jam definitely deserve praise. 

But the best pieces of improv from this show just might be the killer Playing In The Band from set 1, and the Let It Grow>GDTRFB from set 2 - must here stuff without a doubt!
d/s amazing dark star.  so delicate and spacey, hangs on the wispiest of threads throughout.  classic show.  well worth the listen.
4 stars Good performance, but the sound is a bit thin.

MLBJ This show for me begins at the Mind Left body Jam. The first set didn't quite take off for me.
That MLBJ is just stunning. I love how the reviewer below described the dark star that follows: "delicate and spacey, hangs on the wispiest of threads" - very apt. I feel this one may have been a bit subtle for my tastes but the run from Eyes through to GDTRFB is spectacular.
